The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
Archives
				 Todi test
 OUR BUREAU																								Nov. 27: The Central Bureau of Investigation today put Pradip Todi through a lie-detector test at the Central Forensic Science Laboratory in connection with the death of Rizwanur Rahman.																								The Telegraph had earlier reported how Pradip Todi, the uncle of Rizwanurs wife Priyanka, had paid Rs 11 lakh to Pappu.																								The CBI asked Pradip Todi questions on the pay-off that took place in two instalments of Rs 5 lakh and Rs 6 lakh. He was allowed to return to Calcutta in the evening after the test.																								The polygraph examination of Pappu  who has denied taking money from the Todis  will take place tomorrow afternoon.
